entries.name: L1GenesisUpgrade
entries.description: Diamond implementation code to initialize new ZK chains. Used to set their chainID.

entries.name: Diamond
entries.description: The main contract defining the Layer 2. Operator actions like commiting blocks, providing ZK proofs and executing batches ultimately target this contract which then processes transactions. During batch execution it processes L1 --> L2 and L2 --> L1 transactions.

getTransactionFilterer.description: This contract must expose the ITransactionFilterer interface (see Mailbox facet) and is used for censoring transactions pushed from L1 to L2.

IsPorterAvailableStatus.description: zkPorter is a volition-like contruction and changes the zk proof input requirements.

isPermanentRollup.description: true means that the DA mode cannot be changed to Validium in the future. compliant DAValidator pairs for the permanent rollup mode are defined/enforced by the RollupDAManager contract.

getProtocolVersion.description: Protocol version, increments with each protocol upgrade.

getVerifierParams.description: Verifier parameters used for proving batches.

arg.1: . isPermanentRollup was set to true in this contract which prevents changing the DA mode to Validium in the future.

entries.name: ZKsyncOSChainTypeManager
entries.description: [FORK] This contract is not the standard hub contract from the Elastic network but a local fork for ADI chain. Defines L2 diamond contract versions, creation and upgrade data and the proof system for all ZK stack chains connected to it. ZK chains are children of this central contract and can only upgrade to versions that were previously registered here. The current protocol version is 0,30,0.

entries.name: L1NativeTokenVault
entries.description: Canonical central asset escrow for all ZK stack chains.

entries.name: ChainAdminOwnable
entries.description: A governance proxy that lets eth:0xF50293Ac52f987122DcD67Eda0cFb34E9d7a0Cf9 act through it.

directlyReceivedPermissions.description: administrate operator roles for this chain in the ValidatorTimelock, manage fees, apply predefined upgrades, manage censorship through a TransactionFilterer, set DA mode, migrate the chain to whitelisted settlement layers (Chain Admin role).

upgradeTimestamps.description: Timestamps for new protocol version upgrades can be registered here (NOT enforced)

receivedPermissions.description: call the functions to commit, prove, execute and revert L2 batches through the ValidatorTimelock in the ADI Diamond contract.

create new zk chains (based on the current version), register tokens (ZK cluster Admin role).

entries.name: RollupDAManager
entries.description: Simple registry for allowed DA validators for different data availability modes. Scheme 3 is used by default RollupL1DAValidator, the commitment includes EIP-4844 blobs data. Scheme 4 is used only for ZKsyncOS, it is keccak of blob versioned hashes filled with pubdata.

receivedPermissions.description: set the conversion factor for gas token deposits.

entries.name: L1Nullifier
entries.description: Contract responsible for bookkeeping L1 bridging transactions. Used to finalize withdrawals and reclaim failed deposits. Does not escrow funds.

receivedPermissions.description: call the functions to commit, prove, execute and revert L2 batches through the ValidatorTimelock in the ADI Diamond contract.

entries.name: ZKsyncOSDualVerifier
entries.description: A router contract for verifiers. Routes verification requests to THE PLONK VERIFIER ONLY depending on the supplied proof version.

verificationKeyHash.description: Verification key hash for the PLONK verifier ONLY (backwards compatibility).

ctmOwner.description: Contract owner that can add and remove verifiers.

fflonkVerifier0.description: Fflonk verifier with version 0. Verifiers are read from mapping so they are not displayed in an array.

fflonkVerifier1.description: Fflonk verifier with version 1. !MUST BE ZERO, IF NON-ZERO THEN ADD fflonkVerifier2 IN CONFIG! Verifiers are read from mapping so they are not displayed in an array. This value serves as an indicator of a new verifier.

plonkVerifier0.description: Plonk verifier with version 0. Verifiers are read from mapping so they are not displayed in an array.

plonkVerifier1.description: Plonk verifier with version 1. This value serves as an indicator of a new verifier. !MUST BE ZERO, IF NON-ZERO THEN ADD plonkVerifier2 IN CONFIG! Verifiers are read from mapping so they are not displayed in an array.

entries.name: L1MessageRoot
entries.description: Aggregates remote bridge message roots from all ZK stack chains. To be used with the Gateway when deployed.

entries.name: BridgeHub
entries.description: [FORK] This contract is not the standard hub contract from the Elastic network but a local fork for ADI chain. The main registry (hub) for chain contracts (supports more than ADI chain) and central entrypoint for bridge transactions. Stores important mappings like from chainId to diamond address, from chainId to parent CTM, from chainId to base token etc. A clone of Bridgehub is also deployed on each L2 chain, but this clone is only used on settlement layers.

chainsCreated.description: All new chains created go thorugh the central bridgehub and are stored here with their respective STMs.

settlementLayers.description: New settlement layers and their whitelist status. Chains can be migrated to whitelisted settlement layers by their chain admin.

entries.name: Governance
entries.description: Allows scheduling transparent and shadow proposals, 'securityCouncil' role can execute without delay.

receivedPermissions.description: manage the shared ValidatorTimelock contract address and the admin role, register and execute upgrades (and set their deadlines), freeze, revert batches and set permissioned validators and fee params for all connected chains.
manage allowed rollup DA pairs (allowed to be used by rollups in permanent rollup mode).
set critical contract addresses for the shared cluster, register settlement layers, pause and unpause migrations and the bridge and manage zk chain registration.

entries.name: ZKsyncOSVerifierPlonk
entries.description: Verifies a zk-SNARK proof using an implementation of the PlonK proof system.

verificationKeyHash.description: keccak256 hash of the verification keys.

entries.description: Specialized contract for managing chain assets, i.e. chain migrations.

paused.description: this 'paused' is unrelated to migrations and only used for initialization.

migrations.description: zk chain migrations that were started

entries.name: CTMDeploymentTracker
entries.description: Asset deployment tracker where the 'asset' is a ChainTypeManager. The registering of asset IDs for ChainTypeManagers is necessary to be able to migrate them to a given settlement layer, for example the Gateway.

create new zk chains (based on the current version), register tokens (ZK cluster Admin role).

nonce.description: If increased, could mean a new verifier version is registered on DualVerifier.

receivedPermissions.description: pause, unpause and set critical escrow address references.

entries.name: ServerNotifier
entries.description: A simple contract that can be called by the ChainAdmin to emit notifications about chain migrations.

upgradeTimestamps.description: Scheduled upgrade timestamps for specific protocol versions.

entries.name: ValidatorTimelock
entries.description: Intermediary contract between the *Validators* and the central diamond contract that delays block execution (ie withdrawals and other L2 --> L1 messages) by 0s.

entries.name: L1AssetRouter
entries.description: Part of the v26 upgrade: Canonical central asset router for all ZK stack chains (not escrowing funds).

receivedPermissions.description: administrate operator roles for this chain in the ValidatorTimelock, manage fees, apply predefined upgrades, manage censorship through a TransactionFilterer, set DA mode, migrate the chain to whitelisted settlement layers (Chain Admin role).

entries.description: Legacy bridge for depositing ERC20 tokens to ADI Chain.

entries.description: DA verifier specifically for zksync OS chains. It keeps track of blob versioned hashes and checks if blob with particular hash was published.
